OL,5, A senior official previously charged   
OL,6, with vetting the Treasury's plans has  
OL,7, told the BBC chancellor Rishi Sunak can
OL,8, afford to postpone April's tax rises.  
OL,10,FSir Charlie Bean, who recently left the
OL,11,FOffice for Budget Responsibility, said 
OL,12,Fthe plan for an immediate rise may be  
OL,13,Fpolitical rather than economic.        
OL,15,FApril's National Insurance rise will   
OL,16,Ftax the average worker #250 a year, and
OL,17,Fraise costs for firms which hire staff.
OL,19,FThe chancellor maintains the priority  
OL,20,Fhas to be shrinking the deficit.       
